tafsir[12]{c,v,t}:
  25,44,"He hears everything and sees everything and is not unaware of anything."
  25,45,"As Allah is in fact the Sovereign of the universe, His worshipers will surely attain true success and the worshipers of false gods will meet with utter failure."
  25,46,"This verse has a deeper meaning also, though apparently it merely declares that Allah alone has the power to send down rain which makes the land green. The deeper meaning is that the rainfall of the blessed revelation will, in the near future, turn the barren land of Arabia into a garden of knowledge, morality and bring forth a high and righteous civilization."
  25,47,"Latif implies that Allah fulfills His designs in such fine ways that it is difficult to understand them till they become real and apparent."
  25,48,"He alone is All-Sufficient and is not in need of anyone in any way. He is All-praiseworthy because all praise belongs to Him alone whether anyone praises Him or not."
  25,49,"Here “the heaven” implies the whole of the universe above and below the earth where everything is held in its own place and sphere."
  25,50,"That is, though man sees every reality presented by the Prophets, yet he denies it."
  25,51,"That is, the community of every Prophet."
  25,52,"Here the Arabic word mansak has been used in its most comprehensive sense which also includes sacrifice (verse 34). It means service, worship, in short, the entire way of life. The same theme has been expressed in (Surah Al-Maidah, Ayat 48): We prescribed a law and a way of life for each of you."
  25,53,"That is, now you have brought a way of life just as the former Prophets brought ways of life for their people. Therefore the people have no right to dispute with you concerning the law you have brought."
  25,54,"This confirms the explanation given in( E.N. 117) above."
  25,55,"In order to understand the significance of this paragraph, we should keep in view (verse 55- 57) with which this is connected."